10:19.085 --> 10:24.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Turkey's president,
Recep Tayyip
Erdogan, complained of being
left out of the

10:24.557 --> 10:26.025 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Mosul offensive.

10:26.059 --> 10:28.027 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN, Turkish
President (through
translator): Look now.

10:28.061 --> 10:29.829 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The operation in Mosul has
started.

10:29.863 --> 10:31.364 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The operation continues.

10:31.397 --> 10:32.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And what do they say?

10:32.699 --> 10:34.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Turkey shouldn't enter Mosul.

10:34.300 --> 10:35.935 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How can I do that?

10:35.969 --> 10:39.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I share 350 kilometers of border
with Iraq,
and I am under threat on that
border.

10:39.739 --> 10:44.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Erdogan said
again he will
keep some 3,000 Turkish-trained
fighters in

10:44.277 --> 10:47.680 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
northernmost Iraq, despite
objections from
Baghdad.

10:47.714 --> 10:52.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As the fighting starts in
earnest, concerns
are also rising over the more
than one million

10:52.919 --> 10:55.321 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
civilians still in the city.

10:55.355 --> 11:00.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.N. and other organizations
say they're
preparing for up to 200,000
refugees.

11:00.627 --> 11:04.030 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Margaret Warner.

11:04.063 --> 11:09.536 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: And now
perspectives of James
Jeffrey, the U.S. ambassador to
Iraq from

11:09.569 --> 11:15.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
2010 to 2012, and currently
fellow at the
Washington Institute, a think
tank and policy

11:16.009 --> 11:17.076 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
analysis group.

11:17.110 --> 11:18.511 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Welcome to you.

11:18.545 --> 11:20.079 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY, Former U.S.
Ambassador to Iraq:
Thank you, Jeffrey.

11:20.113 --> 11:22.515 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Remind us first
why this city
and its capture is so important.

11:22.549 --> 11:28.354 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: As we just heard,
it's the
last citadel of ISIL in Iraq.

11:28.388 --> 11:30.790 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's the second largest city in
the country.

11:30.823 --> 11:38.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the center of the Sunni
Arab third of
Iraq, if you will, its culture
in that country.

11:38.765 --> 11:45.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And if it falls, then ISIS is
pushed back
to its headquarters deep in
Syria, in Raqqa,

11:45.872 --> 11:47.507 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and that could spell the end of
ISIS.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.375 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, that's a very, very
important development.

11:49.409 --> 11:54.581 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: When ISIS
originally took Mosul
and other cities, the Iraqi army
at that point

11:54.614 --> 11:55.848 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was collapsing.

11:55.882 --> 11:59.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a sense now that it's
strong enough
to do this.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.220 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How difficult will it be?

12:01.254 --> 12:02.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How long do you think it might
take?

12:03.022 --> 12:06.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: As we saw in the
news clip
from Margaret Warner, it's a
very eclectic

12:06.192 --> 12:10.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
force, but it numbers some
50,000 or 60,000
people on the ground, with a
tremendous amount

12:10.563 --> 12:16.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of American and other Western
artillery and
airpower supporting these
people, including,

12:16.769 --> 12:20.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the first time, advisory
units right up
in the front lines.

12:20.873 --> 12:26.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This will take weeks, like the
Fallujah battle
in 2004 also against ISIS's
predecessor, al-Qaida

12:26.679 --> 12:28.448 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in Iraq.

12:28.481 --> 12:30.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, in the end, I think there
is only going
to be one outcome, and that will
be defeat

12:30.883 --> 12:32.652 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of ISIS.

12:32.685 --> 12:35.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: There have also
been reports
inside the city of underground
resistance.

12:36.022 --> 12:40.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When ISIS first went into Mosul,
they were
welcomed by many in the city.

12:40.560 --> 12:42.195 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What happened in the interim?

12:42.228 --> 12:45.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: Al-Qaida has
always had a presence
before it became ISIS in Mosul.

12:45.765 --> 12:49.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was a problem when I was
there in 2010
to 2012.

12:49.836 --> 12:54.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's no doubt that part
of the population
welcomed ISIS when it came in,
because it

12:54.207 --> 12:59.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
felt was being oppressed by the
Shia majority
and the troops sent up by the
Shia -- largely

12:59.145 --> 13:00.313 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Shia government.

13:00.346 --> 13:02.148 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But that changed over time.

13:02.181 --> 13:05.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As in every other city we have
seen that have
been liberated, the people,
regardless of

13:05.785 --> 13:09.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their ethnic and religious
background, welcome
the people who come in.

13:09.522 --> 13:11.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They can't stand living under
ISIS.

13:11.324 --> 13:16.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: That problem,
though, of the
initial welcoming brings us what
might happen

13:16.062 --> 13:18.231 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the aftermath, right, of
retaking Mosul.

13:18.264 --> 13:19.399 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES JEFFREY: Exactly.

13:19.432 --> 13:21.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Because it raises
many other
questions.

13:21.167 --> 13:26.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: Well, the first
one is the
humanitarian, refugee, and food
and relief

13:26.873 --> 13:28.508 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
supplies.

13:28.541 --> 13:32.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is under the control of the
U.N., the
Iraqi government and the Kurdish
regional

13:32.111 --> 13:35.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
government, in coordination with
the Iraqi
government, all being watched
closely by the

13:35.381 --> 13:36.616 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
United States.

13:36.649 --> 13:37.617 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That will be messy.

13:37.650 --> 13:39.452 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It always is.

13:39.485 --> 13:41.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But these people, if there's one
thing, they
have had experience with some
eight million

13:41.688 --> 13:43.523 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
refugees in that region in the
last two years.

13:43.556 --> 13:45.391 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They will, in the end, be able
to do it.

13:45.425 --> 13:47.760 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But there are
fears, though,
about the humanitarian crisis,
right?

13:47.794 --> 13:49.095 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: Oh, absolutely.

13:49.128 --> 13:50.897 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Absolutely.

13:50.930 --> 13:54.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, as I said, we will
get plenty
of stories about people in
inadequate tents,

13:54.834 --> 13:56.869 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
inadequate sewage and such.

13:56.903 --> 14:00.339 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, in the end, I think that
enough food,
supplies will come through.

14:00.373 --> 14:04.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The bigger question is, who will
secure this
place, who will govern it, and
what's going

14:04.377 --> 14:07.246 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to happen to Iraq after the ISIS
threat is
gone?

14:07.280 --> 14:12.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Even including
who marches
into the city in the first
place, right, as

14:12.285 --> 14:16.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Margaret was talking about,
whether it's Iraqi
forces or militia forces.

14:16.222 --> 14:18.024 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES JEFFREY: Exactly.

14:18.057 --> 14:21.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think the deal right now
is that the
Iraqi forces, spearheaded by the
counterterrorism

14:21.661 --> 14:25.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
force, which is very, very good,
and will
have a lot of American advisers
with them

14:25.198 --> 14:29.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and supporting them, will go in
and do the
heavy fighting inside the city.

14:29.302 --> 14:33.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then Sunni police who have been
trained from
the region itself will come in
to secure the

14:34.006 --> 14:35.908 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
city.

14:35.942 --> 14:40.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The trick will be to keep the
Peshmerga forces,
the Kurdish forces, away from
the center of

14:40.313 --> 14:44.083 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the city, but they have
basically agreed to
stop, as I understand it.

14:44.117 --> 14:49.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We don't know if the popular
mobilization
forces, these largely Shia
militias, some

14:49.322 --> 14:53.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of whom are under the thumb of
Iran, will
adhere to this deal, or whether
they will

14:53.526 --> 14:55.027 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
try to push in, as they have
before.

14:55.061 --> 14:56.162 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, that's what
I'm wondering.

14:56.195 --> 14:58.231 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How confident are you or are we?

14:58.264 --> 15:02.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because this is not the first
time that Mosul
has been recaptured, right?

15:02.335 --> 15:07.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, how confident can we be
that, this time,
the forces taking it will get it
right?

15:07.640 --> 15:13.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: Well, some of
these Shia militias,
Ahl al-Haq, the Mahdi Army,
tried to kill

15:13.446 --> 15:17.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
me and my people for years in
Iraq, so I'm
not too confident on anything
they promise,

15:17.850 --> 15:18.818 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to be honest.

15:18.851 --> 15:20.086 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

15:20.119 --> 15:21.954 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: But I will say,
they're not
the majority.

15:21.988 --> 15:27.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Iraqi government and most
Iraqis understand
that they have to bring back the
Sunni Arab

15:27.627 --> 15:30.396 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
20, 25 percent of the
population.

15:30.429 --> 15:34.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It won't work with these Shia
militias running
amok in these areas.

15:34.467 --> 15:39.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, briefly,
ISIS itself,
if it gets kicked out of Mosul,
what then?

15:39.972 --> 15:45.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: It will fall back
on its capital,
Raqqa in Eastern Syria, but it's
a dusty little

15:45.678 --> 15:48.281 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
town compared to Mosul.

15:48.314 --> 15:53.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's being pressed by
Kurdish and Syrian
opposition forces right now from
the north,

15:53.519 --> 15:56.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
as well as American and
American-supported
forces.

15:56.088 --> 15:59.025 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So I think that the end will be
near for ISIS.

15:59.058 --> 16:02.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then we will face all of the
other problems
in the Middle East that ISIS has
covered up

16:02.461 --> 16:03.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
over the last two years.

16:03.963 --> 16:12.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right,
Ambassador James
Jeffrey, thank you very much.

16:12.338 --> 16:15.408 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAMES JEFFREY: Thank you.

16:15.441 --> 16:18.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back to this
country now.

16:18.411 --> 16:23.549 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we heard earlier, Donald
Trump continues
to claim that the presidential
election process

16:23.583 --> 16:25.418 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is rigged against him.

16:25.451 --> 16:28.754 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
That claim seems to be
resonating with some
voters.

16:28.788 --> 16:33.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Just one-third of Republicans
say they have
a great deal of confidence that
their votes

16:33.793 --> 16:36.295 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
will be counted fairly this
election.

16:36.329 --> 16:38.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's according to a recent
Associated Press
poll.

16:38.664 --> 16:41.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For more on all this, we are
joined by Richard
Hasen.

16:41.767 --> 16:45.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's professor of law at the
University of
California, Irvine.

16:45.538 --> 16:48.908 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's author of the Election Law
Blog.

16:48.941 --> 16:51.744 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Al Cardenas is a Republican
strategist.

16:51.777 --> 16:56.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He served as chairman of the
Republican Party
of Florida during the
presidential recount

16:56.616 --> 16:57.583 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in 2000.

16:57.617 --> 17:00.386 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we welcome both of you to
the "NewsHour."

17:00.419 --> 17:02.088 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Al Cardenas, to you first.

17:02.121 --> 17:04.190 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Donald Trump is stepping up
these warnings.

17:04.223 --> 17:08.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He tweeted just a short time ago
-- and I'm
quoting -- he said: "Of course
there's large-scale

17:08.661 --> 17:12.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
voter fraud happening on and
before Election
Day."

17:12.765 --> 17:16.602 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He asked, he said, "Why do
Republican leaders
deny what's going on?

17:16.636 --> 17:18.137 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's so naive."

17:18.170 --> 17:21.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is there large-scale voter fraud
happening
in this country?

17:21.107 --> 17:24.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
AL CARDENAS, Republican
Strategist: Oh, my,
there isn't, hasn't been.

17:24.510 --> 17:29.348 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And our country has been
spending 200-plus
years to get it just right.

17:29.382 --> 17:32.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The checks and balances in the
electoral process
is amazing.

17:32.385 --> 17:35.588 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I know our guest will know more
about it than
I do.

17:35.621 --> 17:41.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we have state elected --
state officials
elected or appointed who are in
charge of

17:41.360 --> 17:43.362 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the overall state process.

17:43.396 --> 17:50.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And every local government,
counties or municipalities,
have supervisor elections who
are elected

17:50.036 --> 17:51.504 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or appointed.

17:51.537 --> 17:55.408 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And then you have local
canvassing boards
made up oftentimes of judges.

17:55.441 --> 17:57.543 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they're part of this whole
processes.

17:57.576 --> 18:02.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everyone who works in these
voting precincts
get trained, gets warned about
violating the

18:02.615 --> 18:07.286 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
laws, gets warned about the
criminal implications
of violating the law.

18:07.320 --> 18:09.121 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have a whole process in
America.

18:09.155 --> 18:15.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in 200-some years, we have
never, ever
had a national election that's
been impacted

18:15.261 --> 18:17.330 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by fraud, not even close.

18:17.363 --> 18:22.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even in Florida, where I served
as chairman
in the famous recount, it -- was
that an issue.

18:22.668 --> 18:25.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Richard Hasen,
what is your
take on this?

18:25.404 --> 18:29.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What is the likelihood that this
process could
be rigged, as Donald Trump
charges?

18:29.108 --> 18:31.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICK HASEN, University of
California, Irvine:
If you're talking about rigging
the way that

18:31.644 --> 18:36.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump is talking about
rigging, I would
say the chances are basically
none.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.050 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's impossible.

18:38.084 --> 18:42.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's talking about people going
into the polling
place and voting five or 10 or
15 times.

18:42.922 --> 18:45.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said this would happen in
certain areas
of Pennsylvania.

18:45.725 --> 18:51.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It seems to be, from what his
surrogate Rudy
Giuliani said, in minority
areas, that Democrats

18:51.764 --> 18:54.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are going to steal the votes by
impersonating
other people.

18:54.967 --> 18:58.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's just now how -- in the
rare times when
voter fraud occur, that's just
not how elections

18:58.971 --> 19:03.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are stolen in this country, and
not on the
kind of scale that could affect
a presidential

19:03.109 --> 19:08.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
election, which would the
cooperation of tens
of thousands of people to try to
commit voter

19:08.581 --> 19:13.586 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
fraud under the noses of
election officials
and party officials who are
watching the whole

19:13.619 --> 19:15.454 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
process.

19:15.488 --> 19:18.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, Richard
Hasen, you say
-- I hear you saying it's
possible to do this

19:18.591 --> 19:20.493 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on a small scale.

19:20.526 --> 19:22.228 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is that right?

19:22.261 --> 19:24.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD HASEN: Well, the kind of
fraud that
we do occasionally see in this
country is

19:24.864 --> 19:26.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
absentee ballot fraud.

19:26.699 --> 19:30.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That occurs because voting takes
place outside
the presence of election
officials.

19:31.003 --> 19:35.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Usually, it involves buying
votes or stealing
ballots out of people's
mailboxes, and then

19:35.641 --> 19:38.010 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
voting them in a particular way.

19:38.044 --> 19:42.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we haven't seen that on the
kind of scale
that could affect a presidential
election.

19:42.615 --> 19:45.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's not the kind of fraud
Donald Trump
has been talking about.

19:45.317 --> 19:49.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was talking about the lack of
voter I.D.,
strict voter I.D. law in
Pennsylvania and

19:50.022 --> 19:53.492 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that would allow someone to go
into the polling
place, and he literally said,
vote five or

19:53.526 --> 19:54.994 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
10 or 15 times.

19:55.027 --> 19:56.762 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That just doesn't happen.

19:56.796 --> 20:01.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For a study I did, I looked from
the 1980s
on to find a single election
anywhere in the

20:01.367 --> 20:05.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
United States where it could
have been called
into question because of that
kind of fraud,

20:05.504 --> 20:07.873 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and I can't find a single
instance anywhere
in the country.

20:07.907 --> 20:11.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That kind of fraud would be a
stupid way to
steal the election, and it just
doesn't happen.

20:11.343 --> 20:14.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Al Cardenas, what
makes you
so confident that this couldn't
happen?

20:14.847 --> 20:16.649 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AL CARDENAS: Well, I lived it in
2000.

20:16.682 --> 20:19.118 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I was party chairman in Florida.

20:19.151 --> 20:24.156 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We had over 250 lawyers involved
and volunteering
in the state.

20:24.190 --> 20:26.459 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We had over 40 lawsuits.

20:26.492 --> 20:28.461 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We had election supervisors.

20:28.494 --> 20:34.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We had judges in every single
county recounting
every vote, tabulating,
retabulating the votes,

20:34.800 --> 20:37.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
determining whether votes were
fairly cast
or not.

20:37.403 --> 20:41.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were challenges being made
by lawyers
from both parties as to votes
that had not

20:41.974 --> 20:43.442 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
been accepted.

20:43.476 --> 20:48.481 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The whole process took 37 days,
thousands
of people, thousands of hours.

20:48.514 --> 20:54.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And not once, not once did we
find intent
to defraud the process
electorally.

20:54.320 --> 20:57.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The press spent millions of
dollars after
that and went through its own
process.

20:57.990 --> 20:59.091 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Yes, they did.

20:59.125 --> 21:00.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AL CARDENAS: And we didn't find
fraud in the
process.

21:00.926 --> 21:06.832 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Let me tell you, Judy, what
really bothers
me here is that America is a
beacon of light

21:06.866 --> 21:11.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for people all throughout the
world who want
their democracies to work our
way.

21:11.270 --> 21:13.973 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We are the idols of most
countries.

21:14.006 --> 21:18.244 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We are asked to oversee
elections in other
countries.

21:18.277 --> 21:21.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We in this country know that
transparency
works.

21:21.447 --> 21:28.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We appreciate and frankly adore
the right
to have the free, peaceful
transfer of power

21:28.954 --> 21:31.824 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from the president to at the
eventual winner.

21:31.857 --> 21:35.427 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We in America have always
celebrated the way
we have elections.

21:35.461 --> 21:42.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To tarnish it with unproven
facts, tarnish
it with accusations, to me, it
is just a shame.

21:42.635 --> 21:44.370 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It shouldn't be done.

21:44.403 --> 21:48.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Richard
Hasen, we also
hear Donald Trump saying to his
supporters

21:48.807 --> 21:53.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from time to time, you need to
go out and
you need to watch people voting
to make sure

21:53.612 --> 21:56.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
everything is being done on the
up and up,
words to that effect.

21:56.982 --> 22:02.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How would that work, for people
to take it
upon themselves to watch the
voting process?

22:02.288 --> 22:06.759 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD HASEN: Well, you know,
there are ways
to watch the voting process.

22:06.792 --> 22:08.594 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are ways to be election
observers.

22:08.627 --> 22:12.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, in most places, you have
Democrats and
Republicans and nonpartisan
groups like the

22:12.231 --> 22:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
League of Women Voters watching
the vote count.

22:14.433 --> 22:16.068 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And those people are trained.

22:16.101 --> 22:17.069 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they know what to do.

22:17.102 --> 22:18.871 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they know not to interfere
with voters.

22:18.904 --> 22:23.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm very concerned that it looks
like Trump
is telling people to take
matters into their

22:23.809 --> 22:25.544 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
own hands.

22:25.578 --> 22:28.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said, after you vote in your
own place,
go to those other areas and see
what's going

22:28.214 --> 22:30.015 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on there.

22:30.049 --> 22:32.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm worried especially in states
where there
is an open-carry law and people
could be taking

22:32.585 --> 22:34.320 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
firearms to the polling place.

22:34.353 --> 22:37.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We need to have an election
where people are
not intimidated, where they feel
free to go

22:37.990 --> 22:40.759 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
into the polling place and vote
their conscience.

22:40.793 --> 22:42.561 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think what he is doing is
dangerous.

22:42.595 --> 22:46.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's dangerous both on after
Election Day
and after Election Day, where,
if he claims

22:46.632 --> 22:51.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the vote count was rigged, who
knows if people
might take into their own hands
to be violent?

22:51.036 --> 22:54.440 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, we really -- we take our
peaceful
transitions for granted.

22:54.473 --> 22:56.175 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think we can't this time
around.

22:56.208 --> 22:59.478 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Just quickly, Al
Cardenas,
how would that work?

22:59.511 --> 23:04.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, if voters in your home
state of Florida
decided they were going to watch
other polling

23:04.550 --> 23:06.352 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
places, what would that mean for
the election?

23:06.385 --> 23:11.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AL CARDENAS: Well, we have a
ballot integrity
initiative every election cycle,
where lawyers

23:11.490 --> 23:13.325 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and others volunteer.

23:13.359 --> 23:15.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They man these phones.

23:15.227 --> 23:20.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If there is a voter that feels
they have been
intimidated, harassed or worse,
they can call

23:20.766 --> 23:21.967 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a number.

23:22.001 --> 23:23.836 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
These lawyers are activated.

23:23.869 --> 23:28.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They go to local elected
officials, and the
matter is immediately
investigated.

23:28.474 --> 23:32.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I can tell you, election after
election -- I
have been chairman of the party
for a long

23:32.511 --> 23:35.481 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
time -- these instances are
rare.

23:35.514 --> 23:41.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, if somebody is going to be
enticed to
go and intimidate voters, well,
that's a whole

23:41.253 --> 23:43.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
different story, as Richard just
mentioned.

23:43.422 --> 23:46.191 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That cannot be tolerated, and
law enforcement
needs to step in.

23:46.225 --> 23:51.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, we're going
to be continuing,
of course, to follow this
between now and

23:51.297 --> 23:52.831 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Election Day three weeks from
tomorrow.

23:52.865 --> 23:55.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Al Cardenas, Richard Hasen, we
thank you both.

23:55.501 --> 23:57.036 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RICHARD HASEN: Thank you.

23:57.069 --> 23:58.804 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AL CARDENAS: Thank you.

23:58.837 --> 24:03.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Online, read how
the Clinton
