30:27.726 --> 30:31.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We may not have seen a gender
gap like this
in -- certainly in the last 30
or 40, 50 -- actually,

30:31.897 --> 30:33.899 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think it goes back 50 years.

30:33.932 --> 30:38.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then the Washington Post
poll that came
out this weekend, when asked do
you think

30:38.370 --> 30:43.809 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that this issue that was raised
in the tape,
his treatment of women, is
important, is it

30:43.842 --> 30:47.612 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a legitimate issue, 55 percent
of voters said
this is a legitimate issue.

30:47.646 --> 30:52.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, writing it off to boys
talking, locker
room talk in the wake, not just
of the audio,

30:52.617 --> 30:56.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but the women who came forward,
I don't think
it's going to do much good.

30:56.054 --> 31:01.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Tam, the
Clinton camp
seems to be -- they're out now
talking about

31:01.193 --> 31:05.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
