expanding the
map.

31:37.829 --> 31:39.598 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Very quickly.

31:39.631 --> 31:41.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: And I think that
what she really
wants to do is run up the score
to show that

31:41.500 --> 31:43.535 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
there is a mandate here.

31:43.568 --> 31:47.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem for that is, she may
get a lot
of votes, a lot of electoral
votes, more than

31:47.239 --> 31:52.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Barack Obama got, but she's
still going to
come into office with an overall
disapproval

31:52.711 --> 31:57.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rating that's higher than
anybody in recent
times has come into the
presidency.

31:57.649 --> 32:03.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, you want more votes, but
it's not necessarily
going to change the way that
people see her,

32:03.155 --> 32:04.656 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not more positively, at least.

32:04.689 --> 32:07.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Amy Walter,
Tamara Keith, thank
you both, Politics Monday.

32:07.959 --> 32:09.694 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: You're welcome.

