35:04.970 --> 35:11.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: In an
increasingly hostile
atmosphere, Syrian musician Nour
Amora has

35:11.910 --> 35:15.013 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
found acceptance.

35:15.046 --> 35:19.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We met Amora just over a year
ago, as the
Danish government slashed
welfare benefits

35:19.417 --> 35:23.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for refugees in an attempt to
make the country
less attractive to asylum
seekers.

35:23.388 --> 35:26.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NOUR AMORA, Syrian Refugee: I
make this concert
to know the people, to know the
artists, the

35:26.691 --> 35:29.160 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
musicians, to make something
with them, to
work, yes.

35:29.194 --> 35:33.999 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't come to Denmark to
sleep.

35:34.032 --> 35:37.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Amora has been
true to his
word.

35:37.502 --> 35:40.905 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He supports himself and his
small family with
two jobs.

35:40.939 --> 35:46.277 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
