fleeing to Europe.

36:18.209 --> 36:21.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LEILA RONG HANNA, Musician:
Because this is
not the perfect life you get.

36:21.813 --> 36:27.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's quite difficult, not only
the journey,
if you survive in the journey,
but also when

36:27.719 --> 36:29.487 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you come here.

36:29.521 --> 36:31.189 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's quite uphill.

36:31.222 --> 36:35.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: That's music to
the ears
of many at the Danish
Parliament, because

36:35.293 --> 36:38.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it's a sign that the country's
policies are
working.

36:38.329 --> 36:43.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the most satisfied is
Martin Henriksen
of the anti-immigrant Danish
People's Party,

36:43.201 --> 36:45.937 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
whose support keeps the
center-right government
in power.

36:45.970 --> 36:48.740 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTIN HENRIKSEN, Danish
People's Party: Well,
last year, about 20,000 asylum
seekers come

36:48.773 --> 36:49.741 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to Denmark.

36:49.774 --> 36:51.476 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And this year, we expected
10,000.

36:51.509 --> 36:56.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This year, we are about around
5,000 at this
time.

36:56.281 --> 36:58.516 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But 5,000 is still too high.

36:58.550 --> 37:02.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We want to -- actually, in the
perfect world,
we want to reduce the numbers,
so that nobody

37:02.420 --> 37:04.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
will come to Denmark as an
asylum seeker.

37:04.589 --> 37:06.458 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So we're not quite there yet.

37:06.491 --> 37:11.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But Peter
Christensen's recently
constituted New Right Party
claims it's even

37:11.896 --> 37:13.698 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
tougher on immigration.

37:13.731 --> 37:18.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's attracted significant
support in recent
surveys after pledging to stop
immigration

37:18.269 --> 37:24.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
altogether, instantly deport
foreigners convicted
of crimes, take Denmark out of
the U.N. Refugee

37:24.309 --> 37:28.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Convention and ban head scarves
in schools
and public offices.

37:28.580 --> 37:31.950 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Critics fear this swing to the
right is reminiscent
of 1930s Europe.

37:31.983 --> 37:35.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER CHRISTENSEN, New Right
Party: I can't
see how that should compare to
the situation

37:35.987 --> 37:43.161 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in the '30s, with the
discrimination of the
Jews, aggressive nations
attacking each other

37:43.194 --> 37:45.029 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the '40s, the Holocaust.

37:45.063 --> 37:47.465 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's no comparison
whatsoever.

37:47.499 --> 37:52.504 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we're talking about is, we
want to implement
a foreign policy that has been
normal until

37:52.537 --> 37:54.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
40, 50 years ago.

37:54.239 --> 37:56.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not -- nobody has the right
to come to
Denmark.

37:56.674 --> 38:00.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have right now because we
are in the
conventions.

38:00.078 --> 38:02.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, I mean, morally, nobody has
the right
to come to Denmark.

38:03.014 --> 38:06.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's not like we are expelling
any people.

38:06.217 --> 38:09.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're just saying we want to
have control
of who comes into our country.

38:09.587 --> 38:15.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Denmark's
deterrence of asylum
seekers has enabled it to it
close 17 refugee

38:15.493 --> 38:19.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
centers, including this one in a
former psychiatric
hospital.

38:19.297 --> 38:23.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The policies worry not only
people fleeing
violence in the Middle East.

38:23.968 --> 38:28.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Chen Man is concerned about the
time it's
taking to process her asylum
application.

38:28.940 --> 38:34.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
